Function to convert pascal_voc to yolo format¶

In [ ]:
def pascal_voc_to_yolo(bbox,image_w, image_h):
    x=np.round((bbox[0]+bbox[2])/2,6)
    y=np.round((bbox[1]+bbox[3])/2,6)
    w=np.round(bbox[2]-bbox[0],6)
    h=np.round(bbox[3]-bbox[1],6)

    #normalize bbox by using image width and height
    x=x/image_w
    y=y/image_h
    w=w/image_w
    h=h/image_h
    
    x=np.round(x,6)
    y=np.round(y,6)
    w=np.round(w,6)
    h=np.round(h,6)
        
    def check_bbox(bbox):
        bbox=list(bbox)
        for i in range(4):
            if (bbox[i]<0.0):
                bbox[i]=0.0
            elif (bbox[i]>1.0):
                bbox[i]=0.99
        return bbox
    
    #box=[x,y,w,h]
    #box=check_bbox(box)
    
    return [x,y,w,h]

Function to create dataset¶

In [ ]:
def create_dataset(base_image_path,df,data_type=None,fold=None):
    image_path="/kaggle/working/yolov5/ship_detection-huggingface/images/"
    label_path="/kaggle/working/yolov5/ship_detection-huggingface/labels/"
    num=1
    if data_type in ['train','valid']:
        for image in tqdm_notebook(df['id'].unique()):
            pic=Image.open(os.path.join(base_image_path,f"{image}"))
            image_w=pic.width
            image_h=pic.height
            bbox_df=df[df['id']==image].iloc[:,1:5]
            yolo_bbox=[]
            for index,row in bbox_df.iterrows():
                
                xmin=row["xmin"]
                ymin=row["ymin"]
                xmax=row['xmax']
                ymax=row['ymax']
                org_bbox=[xmin,ymin,xmax,ymax]
                org_bbox=pascal_voc_to_yolo(org_bbox,image_w,image_h)
    
                def check_bbox(bbox):
                    bbox=list(bbox)
                    for i in range(4):
                        if (bbox[i]<0):
                            bbox[i]=0
                        elif (bbox[i]>1):
                            bbox[i]=1
                    return bbox
                    
                class_value=0
                box_val=[class_value,org_bbox[0],org_bbox[1],org_bbox[2],org_bbox[3]]
                #box_val=check_bbox(box_val)
                yolo_bbox.append(box_val)
            
            
            image_id = image.split('.')[0]
            if not os.path.exists(f"{label_path}{data_type}_fold_{fold}"):
                os.makedirs(f"{label_path}{data_type}_fold_{fold}",exist_ok=True)
            np.savetxt(os.path.join(f"{label_path}{data_type}_fold_{fold}/",f"{num}_{image_id}.txt"),
                                    yolo_bbox, #delimiter=", ",
                                    fmt=["%d", "%f", "%f", "%f", "%f"]
                                    ) 
            
            
            if not os.path.exists(f"{image_path}{data_type}_fold_{fold}"):
                os.makedirs(f"{image_path}{data_type}_fold_{fold}",exist_ok=True)   
            shutil.copyfile(
                        os.path.join(base_image_path, f"{image}"),
                        os.path.join(f"{image_path}{data_type}_fold_{fold}/", f"{num}_{image}"))
            num+=1

Function to create yaml file¶

In [ ]:
def create_yaml(fold):
    yaml_dict = {'train': f"/kaggle/working/yolov5/ship_detection-huggingface/images/train_fold_{fold}",   # path to the train folder
            'val':f"/kaggle/working/yolov5/ship_detection-huggingface/images/valid_fold_{fold}", # path to the val folder
            'nc': 1,                             # number of classes
            'names': ['ship']}
        
    with open(f"/kaggle/working/yolov5/ship_detection_huggingface_fold_{fold}.yaml", 'w') as file:
        documents = yaml.dump(yaml_dict, file)

Train YOLOv5m6 model 5-fold split train data¶

In [ ]:
kfold=KFold(n_splits=5,shuffle=True,random_state=48)
unique_image = pd.DataFrame(train_data['id'].unique(),columns=['id'])
fold=1
for train_index,test_index in kfold.split(train_data['id'].unique()):
    X_train, X_test = unique_image.iloc[train_index], unique_image.iloc[test_index]
    valid_ids = X_test['id'].values
    train_df = train_data.loc[~train_data.id.isin(valid_ids)]
    valid_df = train_data.loc[train_data.id.isin(valid_ids)]
    print(f"Starting Fold: {fold}")
    print("-"*100)
    print("Starting Train Data Preparation")
    create_dataset("/kaggle/working/ship_detection-huggingface/train/",train_df,data_type="train",fold=fold)
    print("Train Data Preparation Done")
    print("-"*100)
    print("Starting Valid Data Preparation")
    create_dataset("/kaggle/working/ship_detection-huggingface/train/",valid_df,data_type="valid",fold=fold)
    print("Valid Data Preparation Done")
    print("-"*100)
    create_yaml(fold)
    print(f"YOLO Model Training For Fold: {fold}")
    !python train.py --epochs 50 --workers 12 --device 0 --batch-size 4 \
    --data ship_detection_huggingface_fold_{fold}.yaml --img 1280 \
    --weights '/yolov5m6.pt' --project ship_detection_huggingface\
    --name yolov5m6_1280px_50_epoch_batch_fold_{fold} --cache --seed 1200 --hyp hyp.scratch-high.yaml
    print(f"End Fold: {fold}")
    print("-"*100)
    clear_output(wait=True)
    fold=fold+1

    X_train, X_test = unique_image.iloc[train_index], unique_image.iloc[test_index]
    valid_ids = X_test['id'].values
    train_df = train_data.loc[~train_data.id.isin(valid_ids)]
    valid_df = train_data.loc[train_data.id.isin(valid_ids)]
    print(f"Starting Fold: {fold}")
    print("-"*100)
    print("Starting Train Data Preparation")

    print("Train Data Preparation Done")

I have used two models yolov5m6 and yolov5x6.¶

The yolov5m6 model took 3h hours and 30 minutes to train the 5-fold data.¶

The yolov5x6 model took 11 hours to train the 5-fold data.¶

I have only minimal system resource, so i have used kaggle free gpu to train the models.¶

Both yolov5ml and yolov5xl model weights are stored in clear-ml model tracking tool.Let's copy the each model experiement id from clear-ml projects page.¶

from clearml import Task
model_path_list=[]
for i in model_list.values():
    prev_task = Task.get_task(task_id=i)
    last_snapshot = prev_task.models['output'][-1]
    local_weights_path = last_snapshot.get_local_copy()
    model_path_list.append(re.findall("/root.*.pt$",local_weights_path))

Function to create a dataframe from predicted results.¶

In [ ]:
def create_sub_mission(yolo_path,test_image_path):
    df=pd.DataFrame(columns=['id','confidence','xmin','ymin','xmax','ymax'])
    for files in tqdm_notebook(os.listdir(yolo_path)):
        txt_file=np.loadtxt(f"{yolo_path}/{files}")
        image_name=files.replace('.txt','.jpg')
        image=Image.open(f"{test_image_path}{image_name}")
        org_img_width=image.width
        org_img_height=image.height
        with open (f"{yolo_path}/{files}") as f:
            lines = f.readlines()
            for line in lines:
                yolo_bbox = np.float64(line.split(" "))
                #yolo_bbox=row.split()
                x_c=yolo_bbox[1]*org_img_width
                y_c=yolo_bbox[2]*org_img_height
                w=yolo_bbox[3]*org_img_width
                h=yolo_bbox[4]*org_img_height
                
                 
                x1=int(round(x_c - w/2))
                y1=int(round(y_c - h/2))
                x2=int(round(x_c + w/2)) 
                y2=int(round(y_c + h/2))
                
                
                
                #class_label="ship"
                conf=yolo_bbox[5]
                res=[image_name,conf,x1,y1,x2,y2]
                df.loc[len(df)] = res
            
    return df

Function to covert the dataframe to submission format.¶

In [ ]:
def result_df(df,missing=False):
    df=copy.deepcopy(df)
    df['confidence']=round(df['confidence'],1)
    cols=['confidence','xmin','ymin','xmax','ymax']
    df[cols] = df[cols].astype('str')
    df['concat']=df[cols].T.agg(' '.join)
    df=df.groupby('id').agg({'concat': lambda x: ', '.join(x.astype(str))}).reset_index()
    df=df.rename(columns={'concat':'label'})
    if missing:
        df=test_image_basic_info.loc[:,['id']].merge(df,how='left',on='id').sort_values('id').\
                                                reset_index().loc[:,['id','label']]
        df['label']=df['label'].fillna("0 0 0 10 10")
    df['id']=df['id'].apply(lambda x:re.sub(".jpg",".png",x))
    return df
